<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8037</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 78</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-21">May 21, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your despatch No. 192 of May
                            4, 1934, concerning the political situation in Nicaragua, the Department
                            approves of your interpretation of its policy as set forth in the
                            penultimate paragraph thereof.</p>
                        <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner
                                    Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>